Peel and finely dice the @onion{1} and the @garlic cloves{2}. Cut the top and bottom off the @red pepper{2} and slice into 1cm strips. Finely chop the @olives{4}(chopped widthways) (it'll make the final presentation nicer!). Pick the @mint{3%sprigs} leaves and then roughly chop them.

> Our Head Chef is basically obsessed with Mexican food and will find any excuse 
> to cook it. In the interests of diversity Sous Chef Rachel has been trying 
> to wean him off, but thought it best not to go cold turkey. That's when she 
> hit upon this Greek twist on nachos grande and it became an instant winner 
> down at the Farm!

Toss the red pepper in @olive oil{1%tbsp} and @salt{1/4%tsp}. Cook on the top 
shelf of your #grill{} on its highest setting for ~{7-10%minutes} until just 
charred at the edges.

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a pan over a medium heat. Add the onion and cook 
for ~{3-4%minutes} until soft. Add the garlic and cook for another 
~{1%minute}. Next, add the @tomato puree{2%tbsp} and cook for 
~{1%minute}.

Turn the heat up to high. Add the @lamb mince{500%g}, the @dried oregano{1%tsp}, 
@salt{1/2%tsp} and a few good grinds of @black pepper{}. Cook for 
~{6-7%minutes}, breaking the mince up with a #wooden spoon{}. Next, add the 
olives and cook for a further ~{1-2%minutes}.

The peppers should now be ready. Put them to the side and pre-heat your 
#oven{} to 200 degrees. Cut the @wholemeal pita bread{4} in half and then split 
down the middle. Cut each half into triangles, brush with a little 
@olive oil{} and sprinkle with @salt{1/4%tsp}. Lay on a #baking tray{} and 
cook in the oven for ~{5-10%minutes} until crispy (like tortilla chips).

Cut the @cucumber{1/2} in half lengthways and scoop out the seeds with a 
#tsp{}. Cut each half into 1cm strips and then chop into approx 1cm cubes. 
Mix the cucumber with the @Greek style yoghurt{5%tbsp}, 3/4 of the chopped 
mint, @salt{1/4%tsp} and @lemon juice{1%tsp} from @lemon{1/2}.

Toast the @pine nuts{3%tbsp} in a dry pan over a medium heat for a few minutes 
until golden brown.

> Watch your nuts like a culinary squirrel, as the moment your back is turned 
> they can burn!

Stack your pita crisps with the lamb, roasted peppers and tzatziki. Top with 
the remaining chopped mint and the pine nuts.